## Resource Management

### Memory Budget

| Component | Typical Budget | Monitoring |
|-----------|---------------|------------|
| Model weights | 50-500 MB | RSS memory |
| Feature cache | 100-500 MB | Cache size metrics |
| Request buffers | 50-100 MB | Queue depth |
| Overhead | 200 MB | Total - components |

### Scaling Patterns

- [ ] Horizontal scaling via load balancer for stateless inference
- [ ] GPU sharing for multiple small models
- [ ] Request queuing with backpressure for burst traffic
- [ ] Auto-scaling based on latency P99 or queue depth

---

## Monitoring in Production

### Required Metrics

| Metric | Alert Threshold | Dashboard |
|--------|-----------------|-----------|
| Prediction latency P50/P95/P99 | P99 > 2x baseline | Yes |
| Request throughput (req/s) | Sudden drop > 50% | Yes |
| Error rate | > 1% | Yes |
| Model load time | > 60s | Yes |
| Prediction distribution | KS divergence > 0.1 | Yes |
| Feature availability | Missing > 5% | Yes |

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Loading model on every request | Extreme latency | Load once at startup |
| No health checks | Silent failures | Liveness + readiness probes |
| Unbounded request queue | OOM under load | Backpressure with max queue size |
| No shadow/canary testing | Risky deployment | Always shadow first |
